		<!-- javascript files -->
			<!-- important variable / global variables / constants -->
			<script>
				const SCREEN_WIDTH = 640;
				const SCREEN_HEIGHT = 480;
				
				const GROUND_LEVEL = SCREEN_HEIGHT - 99;
				
				const CHARACTER_WIDTH = 25;
				const CHARACTER_HEIGHT = 85;
				
				const GUN_WIDTH = 18;
				const GUN_HEIGHT = 10;
				
				const MAX_ROW = 3;
				const MAX_COL = 4;
				
				const ANIMATION_DELAY = 20;
				
				const MAX_AMMO = 10; // 10 bullets
				
				const MAX_BULLET_SPEED = 12;
				
				let STARTING_MAGAZINE = 3;
				
				let BULLET_SPEED = 10;
				const MIN_BULLET_SPEED = 5;
				
				const V_WIDTH = 40;
				const V_HEIGHT = 100;
				
				let bullet_damage = 1;
				
				const MAX_NO_OF_HURDLES = 5;
				
			</script>
			
			<!-- gathering or selecting elements -->
			<script>
				const Canvas = document.getElementById ("Canvas");
				const ctx = Canvas.getContext ("2d");
				
			</script>
			<!-- image manager -->
			<script>
				function ImageManager (fileName) {
					this.ImageManager = document.createElement ("img");
					this.ImageManager.src = fileName;

					this.ImageManager.style.display = "none";

					document.body.appendChild (this.ImageManager);

					
					// renders the image
					this.render = function (x, y, width, height, dest_x, dest_y, dest_width, dest_height) {
						ctx.drawImage (this.ImageManager, x, y, width, height, dest_x, dest_y, dest_width, dest_height);
					}
				}
			</script>
			
			<!-- game physics -->
			<script>
				// If x and y are CENTER points -- this is AI generated and also, this code was taken as an example from Lazy Foo's SDL2/ Game making tutorial
				// here is the link: https://lazyfoo.net/tutorials/SDL/27_collision_detection/index.php
				function checkCollision(a, b) {
				  // Calculate sides of rect A
				  const leftA   = a.x;
				  const rightA  = a.x + a.width;
				  const topA    = a.y;
				  const bottomA = a.y + a.height;

				  // Calculate sides of rect B
				  const leftB   = b.x;
				  const rightB  = b.x + b.width;
				  const topB    = b.y;
				  const bottomB = b.y + b.height;

				  // Check for separation on any side — if found, no collision
				  if (bottomA <= topB)    return false;
				  if (topA >= bottomB)    return false;
				  if (rightA <= leftB)    return false;
				  if (leftA >= rightB)    return false;

				  // No separation detected — collision!
				  return true;
				}
				
				// function to check for collision - point
				function checkPointCollision (x, y, box1) {
					if ((x < box1.x) && (x > box1.x + box1.width) && (y < box1.y) && (y > box1.y + box1.height )) {
						return false;
					}
					
					return true;
				}
			</script>
			
			<!-- making the character -->
			<script>
			
				function CharacterManager (charImage, charImage_l) {
					this.action = "idle";
					this.animeDelay = 0;
					this.Speed = 5;
					this.direction = "right";
					let i = 0;
					
					this.health = 10;
					
					this.magazine = 3;
					
					this.jumping = false;
					this.jump_up = true;
					this.jump_down = false;
					
					this.JUMP_SPEED = 3;
					
					this.x = 10;
					this.y = GROUND_LEVEL - CHARACTER_HEIGHT;
					this.width = CHARACTER_WIDTH;
					this.height = CHARACTER_HEIGHT;
					
					this.conditions = ["idle", "jump_up", "jump_down", "run"];
					this.clip = [
						[
							[0, 0, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 1, 0, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 2, 0, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], // idle
						], 
						[
							[0, CHARACTER_HEIGHT, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 1, CHARACTER_HEIGHT, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 2, CHARACTER_HEIGHT, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], // JUMPING UP
						],
						[						
							[0, CHARACTER_HEIGHT * 2, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 1, CHARACTER_HEIGHT * 2 , CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 2, CHARACTER_HEIGHT * 2, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], // JUMPING DOWN
						],
						[						
							[0, CHARACTER_HEIGHT * 3, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 1, CHARACTER_HEIGHT * 3, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], [CHARACTER_WIDTH * 2, CHARACTER_HEIGHT * 3, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT], // JUMPING UP
						]
					];
					
					
					this.doingWhat = function (v_stun, gun) {
						<!-- this.action = act; -->
						this.isDead (v_stun);
						this.showText(gun);
						// if the direction is right
						if (this.direction == "right") {
							if (this.action == this.conditions[0]) {
								charImage.render (this.clip[0][i][0], this.clip[0][i][1], this.clip[0][i][2], this.clip[0][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);
							}
							if (this.action == this.conditions[1]) {
								charImage.render (this.clip[1][i][0], this.clip[1][i][1], this.clip[1][i][2], this.clip[1][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);
								
								
							}
							if (this.action == this.conditions[2]) {
								charImage.render (this.clip[2][i][0], this.clip[2][i][1], this.clip[2][i][2], this.clip[2][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);
								
							}
							if (this.action == this.conditions[3]) {
								charImage.render (this.clip[3][i][0], this.clip[3][i][1], this.clip[3][i][2], this.clip[3][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);
							}
							
							if (this.animeDelay > ANIMATION_DELAY) {
								i++;
								this.animeDelay = 0;
							}
							
							if (i >= MAX_ROW) {
								i = 0;
								this.action = "idle";
							}
							
							this.animeDelay ++;
						}
						
						// if the direction is left
						if (this.direction == "left") {
							if (this.action == this.conditions[0]) {
								charImage_l.render (this.clip[0][i][0], this.clip[0][i][1], this.clip[0][i][2], this.clip[0][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);

							}
							if (this.action == this.conditions[1]) {
								charImage_l.render (this.clip[1][i][0], this.clip[1][i][1], this.clip[1][i][2], this.clip[1][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);

								
							}
							if (this.action == this.conditions[2]) {
								charImage_l.render (this.clip[2][i][0], this.clip[2][i][1], this.clip[2][i][2], this.clip[2][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);

							}
							if (this.action == this.conditions[3]) {
								charImage_l.render (this.clip[3][i][0], this.clip[3][i][1], this.clip[3][i][2], this.clip[3][i][3], this.x, this.y, CHARACTER_WIDTH, CHARACTER_HEIGHT);
							}
							
							if (this.animeDelay > ANIMATION_DELAY) {
								i++;
								this.animeDelay = 0;
							}
							
							if (i >= MAX_ROW) {
								i = 0;
								this.action = "idle";
							}
							
							this.animeDelay ++;
						}
					}
					
					this.charJumping = function () {
						if (this.jumping) {
							if (this.jump_up) {
								this.y -= this.JUMP_SPEED;
								
								if (this.y < 195) {
									this.jump_down = true;
									this.jump_up = false;
								}
								
							}
							if (this.jump_down) {
								this.y += this.JUMP_SPEED;
								
								if (this.y >= (GROUND_LEVEL - CHARACTER_HEIGHT)) {
									this.jump_up = true;
									this.jump_down = false;
									this.jumping = false;
								}
							}
						}
						
					}
					
					this.isDead = function (karma) {
						if (this.health <= 0) {
							if (karma.health > 5) {
								karma.health -= Math.floor (karma.health * 0.2);
								this.health = Math.floor (0.2 * karma.health);
								<!-- hero_karma.play (); -->
								
								if (Math.floor (Math.random () * 2) == 1) {
									hero_karma.play ();
								} else {
									hero_pain.play ();
								}
							} else {
								// game over stop the loop and all
								quit = true;
								
								ctx.clearRect (0, 0, SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT);
								
								ctx.font = "52px Arial";
								ctx.fillStyle = "black";
								ctx.fillRect (0, 0, SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT);
								
								ctx.fillStyle = "white";
								ctx.fillText ("GAME OVER !!! ", 320, SCREEN_HEIGHT /2);
								
								ctx.font = "16px Arial";
								ctx.fillStyle = "white";
								ctx.fillText ("Press 'reload' to play again (loop)", 10, 400);
								
								
							}
							// show the text here
							
							// game over text
							// pain sound
							<!-- hero_pain.play (); -->
						}
					}
					
					this.showText = function (gun) {
					
						ctx.font = "10px Arial";
						ctx.fillStyle = "yellow";
						ctx.fillText(this.health, this.x + 10, this.y - 10);
						heartImage.render (0, 0, 48, 48, this.x - 24, this.y - 20, 20, 20);
						
						bulletImage.render (0, 0, 16, 16, this.x + 16, this.y - 10, 20, 20);
						<!-- if (gun.shot_ammo > 5) { -->
							<!-- ctx.fillStyle = "red"; -->
						<!-- } else { -->
							<!-- ctx.fillStyle = "yellow"; -->
						<!-- } -->
						
						ctx.fillStyle = "yellow";
						
						ctx.fillText (10 - gun.shot_ammo, this.x + 36, this.y - 10);
						
						if (gun.reloading) {
							ctx.fillText ("Reloading..", this.x - 10, this.y - 48);
						}
						
					}
				}
				
				// class for v_stone
				function V_stone () {
					this.x = 0;
					this.y = 0;
					
					this.health = 40;
					
					this.width = V_WIDTH;
					this.height = V_HEIGHT;
					
					this.MIN_SPEED = 3;
					this.MAX_SPEED = 6;
					
					this.MIN_LEFT_DISTANCE = 1;
					this.MIN_RIGHT_DISTANCE = 1;
					
					this.MIN_TIMEOUT = 3200;
					this.MAX_TIMEOUT = 12000; // 12000 - 12 seconds
					
					this.v_speed = this.MIN_SPEED;
					
					this.Time_Out = this.MIN_TIMEOUT;
					
					<!-- this.max_left_distance = Math.floor (Math.random () * 210); -->
					<!-- if (this.max_left_distance < this.MIN_LEFT_DISTANCE) { -->
						<!-- this.max_left_distance = this.MIN_LEFT_DISTANCE; -->
					<!-- } -->
					
					<!-- this.max_right_distance = Math.floor (Math.random () * 210); -->
					<!-- if (this.max_right_distance < this.MIN_RIGHT_DISTANCE) { -->
						<!-- this.max_right_distance = this.MIN_RIGHT_DISTANCE; -->
					<!-- } -->
					this.damage = 5;
					this.condition = false;
					this.direction = "right"; // "left"
					
					<!-- this.chase = false; -->
					
					this.setHigherBeingTimeout = function () {
						
						this.Time_Out = Math.floor (Math.random () * this.MAX_TIMEOUT);
						if (this.Time_Out < this.MIN_TIMEOUT) {
							this.Time_Out = this.MIN_TIMEOUT;
						}
					}
					
					this.setHigherBeing = function (lHurdles) {
						chaseSound.stop();
						this.y = GROUND_LEVEL - V_HEIGHT;
						this.behaveRandom ();
						
						// taking random number
						if (Math.floor (Math.random () * 3) == 1) {
							for (let i = 0; i < MAX_NO_OF_HURDLES; i++) {
								lHurdles[i].setHurdles ();
								lHurdles[i].showHurdles = true;
							}
						}
					
						this.max_left_distance = Math.floor (Math.random () * 300);
						if (this.max_left_distance < this.MIN_LEFT_DISTANCE) {
							this.max_left_distance = this.MIN_LEFT_DISTANCE;
						}
						
						this.max_right_distance = 180 + Math.floor (Math.random () * 300);
						if (this.max_right_distance < this.MIN_RIGHT_DISTANCE) {
							this.max_right_distance = this.MIN_RIGHT_DISTANCE;
						}
						
						this.v_speed = Math.floor (Math.random () * this.MAX_SPEED);
						if (this.v_speed < this.MIN_SPEED) {
							this.v_speed = this.MIN_SPEED;
						}

					}
					
					
					this.showHigherBeing = function (heroBody) {
						this.isDead (heroBody);
						this.showText ();
						if (this.condition) {
							// peeking from left
							if (this.direction == "left") {							
								vImage_left.render (0, 0, V_WIDTH, V_HEIGHT, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);
								if (heroBody.x - this.x < 150) {
									chaseSound.play ();
									// throw hurdles
								}
								<!-- console.log ("The program is reading here left"); -->
							} else if (this.direction == "right") {// peek from right
								vImage_right.render (0, 0, V_WIDTH, V_HEIGHT, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);
								
								if (this.x - heroBody.x < 150) {
									chaseSound.play();
									// throw hurdles
								}
								<!-- console.log ("The program is reading here right"); -->
							}
							this.conditionToShowHigherBeing ();
						}
						
					}
					
					// condition to show the higher being
					this.conditionToShowHigherBeing = function () {
						if (this.direction == "left") {
							this.x += this.v_speed;
							if (this.x >= this.max_left_distance) {
								this.condition = false;
								this.y = 0;
							}
						} else if (this.direction == "right") {
						<!-- } else { -->
							this.x -= this.v_speed;
							if (this.x <= this.max_right_distance) {
								this.condition = false;
								this.y = 0;
							}
						}
					}
					
					// travel distance
					this.behaveRandom = function () {
						<!-- this.max_left_distance = Math.floor (Math.random () * 210); -->
						<!-- this.max_right_distance = 420 + Math.floor (Math.random () * 210); -->
						<!-- this.v_speed = Math.floor (Math.random () * 20); -->
						let directionRando = Math.floor (Math.random () * 2);
						
						if (directionRando == 0) {
							this.direction = "left";
							this.x = 0 - V_WIDTH;
						} else if (directionRando == 1) {
							this.direction = "right";
							this.x = SCREEN_WIDTH;
						}
					}
					
					this.isDead = function (heroBody) {
						if (this.health <= 0) {
							this.health = 50;
							// pain sound
							if (Math.floor (Math.random () * 2 ) == 1) {
								karma_whisper.play ();
							} else {
								karma_laugh.play ();
							}
							// text saying it ain't that easy
						}
					}
					
					this.showText = function () {
						ctx.font = "24px Arial";
						
						ctx.fillStyle = "Cyan";
						
						heartImage.render (0, 0, 48, 48, this.x, this.y - 75, 24, 24);
						ctx.fillText (this.health, this.x, this.y - 25);
					}
				}
				
				function Hurdles () {
					this.x = 0;
					this.y = 0;
					this.width = 0;
					this.height = 0;
					
					this.MAX_WIDTH = 30; this.MIN_WIDTH = 20;
					this.MAX_HEIGHT = 30; this.MIN_HEIGHT = 20;
					this.MAX_SPEED = 6; this.MIN_SPEED = 3;
					
					this.direction = "right"; // left - if the direction of the hurdle and the player is same then there will not be a collision
					this.speed = this.MIN_SPEED;
					
					this.showHurdles = false;
					
					// method to set the hurdles
					this.setHurdles = function () {
						hurdle_incoming.play();
						this.width = Math.floor (Math.random () * this.MAX_WIDTH);
						if (this.width < this.MIN_WIDTH) {this.width = this.MIN_WIDTH};
						this.height = Math.floor (Math.random () * this.MAX_HEIGHT);
						if (this.height < this.MIN_HEIGHT) {this.height = this.MIN_HEIGHT};
						
						// getting the direction
						let directionRando = Math.floor (Math.random () * 4);
						
						switch (directionRando) {
							case 0: // up
								this.direction = "up";
								this.x = Math.floor (Math.random() * (SCREEN_WIDTH - this.width));
								this.y = SCREEN_WIDTH + this.height;
								break;
							case 1: // down
								this.direction = "down";
								this.x = Math.floor (Math.random () * (SCREEN_WIDTH - this.width));
								this.y = 0 - this.height;
								break;
							case 2:
								this.direction = "left";
								this.x = SCREEN_WIDTH;
								this.y = GROUND_LEVEL - this.height;
								break;
							case 3:
								this.direction = "right";
								this.x = 0;
								this.y = GROUND_LEVEL - this.height;
								break;
							
						}
						
						
						<!-- this.y = 0 - this.height; -->
						
						this.speed = Math.floor (Math.random () * this.MAX_SPEED);
						if (this.speed < this.MIN_SPEED) {
							this.speed = this.MIN_SPEED;
						}
					}
					
					// method to reset the hurdles
					this.resetHurdles = function () {
						this.width = 0;
						this.height = 0;
						this.x = 0;
						this.y = 0;
						
						this.direction = "right";
						
						this.speed = this.MIN_SPEED;
						
						this.showHurdles = false;
					}
					
					// method to check collision of the hurdles with the the hero
					this.checkHurdleCollision = function (heroBody) {
						if (this.showHurdles) { // if only the hurdles are showing up
							// if the hurdle's direction and hero's direction are same not same then check for collision
							if (this.direction != heroBody.direction) {							
								if (checkCollision (this, heroBody)) {
									// if collision
									hitArray[Math.floor(Math.random () * 5)].play ();
									this.showHurdles = false;
									this.resetHurdles ();
									heroBody.health --;
								}
							}
						}
					}
					
					
					// method to move the hurdle
					this.moveHurdle = function () {
						if (this.direction == "left") {
							this.x -= this.speed;
						} else if (this.direction == "right") {
							this.x += this.speed;
						} else if (this.direction == "up") {
							this.y -= this.speed;
						} else if (this.direction == "down" ) {
							this.y += this.speed;
						}
					}
					
					// method to update the hurdle every time
					this.updateHurdle = function () {
						// updating the position of the hurdle
						if (this.showHurdles) {
							this.moveHurdle ();
							
							if (this.direction == "left") {
								hurdle_rock.render (0, 0, 250, 175, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);
								<!-- hurdle_rockSound.play(); -->
							}
							if (this.direction == "right") {
								hurdle_rock.render (0, 0, 144, 144, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);
								<!-- hurdle_ballSound.play (); -->
							}
							if (this.direction == "up") {
								hurdle_rock.render (0, 0, 121, 250, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);
								<!-- hurdle_rocketSound.play (); -->
							}
							if (this.direction == "down") {
								hurdle_rock.render (0, 0, 233, 400, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);
								<!-- hurdle_meteorSound.play (); -->
							}
						
						}
						
						
					}
					
				}
			</script>
			
			<!-- class for audio manager -->
			<script>
				function AudioManager (fileName) {
					this.AudioManager = document.createElement ("audio");
					this.AudioManager.src = fileName;
					this.AudioManager.setAttribute ("controls", "none");
					this.AudioManager.setAttribute ("preload", "auto");
					
					this.AudioManager.style.display = "none";
					
					document.body.appendChild (this.AudioManager);
					
					this.play = function () {
						this.AudioManager.play ();
					}
					
					this.stop = function () {
						this.AudioManager.pause ();
					}
				}
			</script>
			
			
			<!-- class for gun manager -->
			<script>
				function Bullet (direction, x, y, width, height) {
					this.showBullet = false;
					this.direction = direction;
					this.x = x;
					this.y = y;
					this.width = width;
					this.height = height;
				}
			
				function GunManager (hero_Insc/* taking hero's instance*/, /* guns image*/gun_right, gun_left) {
					let gunPosition_y = CHARACTER_HEIGHT / 2;
					let gunPosition_x = CHARACTER_WIDTH / 2;
					this.x = hero_Insc.x + gunPosition_x;
					this.y = hero_Insc.y + gunPosition_y;
					
					// about bullet
					this.shot_ammo = 0;
					this.bullet_count = 0;
					this.BULLET_WIDTH = 5;
					this.BULLET_HEIGHT = 5;
					this.BULLET_COLOR = "yellow";
					
					this.reloading = false;
					
					this.bulletArray = [];

					
					
					this.isEquipped = true; // false
					this.gunDirection = hero_Insc.direction;
					
					
					this.branchBulletReload = function (bulletArray, shot_ammo) {
						this.bulletArray.length = 0;
						this.shot_ammo = 0;
						this.reloading = false;
					}
					
					this.reloadBullet = function () {
					
						if (this.reloading) {
						
							reload.play ();
							setTimeout (this.branchBulletReload.bind(this), 3000);
							<!-- this.shot_ammo = 0; -->
							
						}
					}
					
					this.shootBullet = function () {
						if (this.shot_ammo < MAX_AMMO && this.isEquipped) {						

							// tell to reload
							this.shot_ammo ++;
							<!-- ctx.fillStyle = this.BULLET_COLOR; -->
							
							if (hero_Insc.direction == "left") {
								this.bulletArray.push (new Bullet("left", this.x, this.y, this.BULLET_WIDTH, this.BULLET_HEIGHT));
								this.bulletArray[this.bulletArray.length - 1].showBullet = true;
							} else if (hero_Insc.direction == "right") {
								this.bulletArray.push (new Bullet("right", this.x, this.y, this.BULLET_WIDTH, this.BULLET_HEIGHT));
								this.bulletArray[this.bulletArray.length - 1].showBullet = true;
							}	
							
							shoot.play ();
						} else if (this.shot_ammo >= MAX_AMMO && this.isEquipped) {
							// cannot shot more ammo
							empty.play ();
							this.reloading = true;
							
							this.reloadBullet ();
						}
					
					}
					
					this.bulletCollision = function (heroBody, vBody) {
						// checking for bullet collision
							// collision with another bullet
						for (let i = 0; i < this.bulletArray.length; i++) {
							<!-- if (this.bulletArray[i].showBullet) {							 -->
								for (let j = 0; j < this.bulletArray.length; j++) {
									if (i != j) {
										if (this.bulletArray[i].direction != this.bulletArray[j].direction && this.bulletArray[j].showBullet) {										
											if (checkCollision (this.bulletArray[i], this.bulletArray[j])) { // if the collision is true
												this.bulletArray[i].showBullet = false; // we don't show the bullets
												this.bulletArray[i].y = 0;
												this.bulletArray[j].y = 0;
												this.bulletArray[j].showBullet = false; // we don't show the bullets
												
												explosion.play ();
											}
										}
									}
								}
								
								// check collision with the hero's body
								for (let j = 0; j < this.bulletArray.length; j++) {
								
									if (checkCollision (this.bulletArray[j], heroBody) && (this.bulletArray[j].direction != heroBody.direction) && (this.bulletArray[j].showBullet)) {
										// decrease hero's health and disappear the bullet
										
										if (this.bulletArray[i].direction != heroBody.direction && this.bulletArray[i].showBullet) {
											heroBody.health -= bullet_damage;
											this.bulletArray[j].showBullet = false;
											this.bulletArray[j].y = 0;
											// making hit sound
											hitArray[Math.floor(Math.random() * 5)].play();
											
											<!-- console.log ("The value of this bullet is " + this.bulletArray[j].y); -->
										}
									}
								}
								
								// checking collision with the villain's body
								if (checkCollision (this.bulletArray[i], vBody) && vBody.condition && (vBody.direction == this.bulletArray[i].direction)) {
									// decrease villain's health and make the bullet disappear
									this.bulletArray[i].showBullet = false;
									this.bulletArray[i].y = 0;
									vBody.condition = false;
									
									vBody.y = 0;
									
									vBody.health -= bullet_damage;
									
									// making hit sound
									hitArray[Math.floor(Math.random() * 5)].play();
									vLaugh.play();
								}
							<!-- } -->
						}
						
					}
					
					this.renderBullet = function (heroBody, vBody) {
						ctx.fillstyle = this.BULLET_COLOR;
						for (let i = 0; i < this.bulletArray.length; i++) {
							if (this.bulletArray[i].direction == "right") {
								this.bulletArray[i].x += BULLET_SPEED;
								
								// if the bullet is out of bounds
								if (this.bulletArray[i].x > SCREEN_WIDTH) {
									this.bulletArray[i].x = 0 - this.BULLET_WIDTH;
								}
								
								// check collision here
								this.bulletCollision (heroBody, vBody);
								
								// rendering if the show bullet is true
								if (this.bulletArray[i].showBullet) {								
									ctx.fillRect (this.bulletArray[i].x, this.bulletArray[i].y, this.BULLET_WIDTH, this.BULLET_HEIGHT);					
								}
							} else if (this.bulletArray[i].direction == "left") {
								this.bulletArray[i].x -= BULLET_SPEED;
								
								// if the bullet is out of bounds
								if (this.bulletArray[i].x + this.BULLET_WIDTH < 0) {
									this.bulletArray[i].x = SCREEN_WIDTH;
								}
								
								// check collision here
								this.bulletCollision (heroBody, vBody);
								
								// rendering if the show bullet is true
								if (this.bulletArray[i].showBullet) {								
									ctx.fillRect (this.bulletArray[i].x, this.bulletArray[i].y, this.BULLET_WIDTH, this.BULLET_HEIGHT);
								}
							}
							
						}

					}
					// render, gun
					this.renderGun = function () {
						this.gunDirection = hero_Insc.direction;
						this.y = hero_Insc.y + gunPosition_y;
						
						if (this.isEquipped) {
							// render the gun
							if (this.gunDirection == "right") {
								this.x = hero_Insc.x + gunPosition_x;
								gun_right.render (0, 0, GUN_WIDTH, GUN_HEIGHT, this.x, this.y, GUN_WIDTH, GUN_HEIGHT);
							} else if (this.gunDirection == "left") {
								gun_left.render (0, 0, GUN_WIDTH, GUN_HEIGHT, this.x, this.y, GUN_WIDTH, GUN_HEIGHT);
								this.x = hero_Insc.x - gunPosition_x;
							}

						}
					}
				}
				
				// class for power ups
				function Powerup () {
					this.x = 0;
					this.y = 0;
					
					this.width = 24;
					this.height = 24;
					
					this.show = false;
					this.type = "life"; // bullet
					
					this.onDisplay = false;
					
					this.MAXIMUM_BULLET_DAMAGE = 4;
					this.MAXIMUM_HEALTH = 12;
					
					this.DEFAULT_BULLET_DAMAGE = 1;
					this.DEFAULT_HEALTH = 10;
					
					this.getPowerup = function () {
						if (!this.onDisplay) {						
							if (Math.floor (Math.random () * 4) == 1) {
								this.onDisplay = true;
								this.x = Math.floor (Math.random () * (SCREEN_WIDTH - this.width));
								this.y = GROUND_LEVEL - this.width;
								// throwing the power up
								let powerRando = Math.floor (Math.random () * 2);
								
								switch (powerRando) {
									case 1:
										this.type = "bullet";
										break;
									case 0:
										this.type = "life";
										break;
									case 2:	
										this.type = "magazine";
										break;
								}
							}
						}
					}
					
					this.renderPowerup = function (heroBody) {
						if (this.onDisplay) {
							// rendering
							if (this.type == "life") {
								// rendering heart
								heartImage.render (0, 0, 48, 48, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.width);
							} else if (this.type == "bullet") {
								bulletImage.render (0, 0, 16, 16, this.x, this.y, this.width, this.width);
							}
							
							// detecting collision
							if (checkCollision (heroBody, this)) {
								if (this.type == "life") {
									heroBody.health ++;
									if (heroBody.health >= this.MAXIMUM_HEALTH) {
										heroBody.health = this.MAXIMUM_HEALTH;
									}
									powerup.play();
									this.onDisplay = false;
									this.y = 0;
								} else if (this.type == "bullet") {
									bullet_damage ++;
									if (bullet_damage >= this.MAXIMUM_BULLET_DAMAGE) {
										bullet_damage = this.MAXIMUM_BULLET_DAMAGE;
									}
									powerup.play();
									this.onDisplay = false;
									this.y = 0;
								}
							}
						}
					}
				}
			</script>
			
			
			<!-- make instances of the class -->
			<script>
				let background = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				let heroImage_right = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				let heroImage_left = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				let gunImage_right = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				let gunImage_left = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				
				let vImage_left = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				let vImage_right = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				
				let heartImage = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				let bulletImage = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				
				<!-- let hurdle_rocket = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64, "); -->
				let hurdle_rock = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,");
				<!-- let hurdle_ball = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,"); -->
				<!-- let hurdle_meteor = new ImageManager ("data:image/png;base64,"); -->
				
				// character
				let hero = new CharacterManager (heroImage_right, heroImage_left);
				
				// gun
				let gun = new GunManager (hero, gunImage_right, gunImage_left);
				
				// karma - villain
				let karma = new V_stone ();
				
				
				// audio instances
				let click = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64,");
				let shoot = new AudioManager ("data:audio/wav;base64,");
				let explosion = new AudioManager ("data:audio/wav;base64,");
				let jump = new AudioManager ("data:audio/wav;base64, ");
				let reload = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let empty = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let gun_equip = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let gun_unequip = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				
				let powerup = new AudioManager ("data:audio/wav;base64, ");
				let hurdle_incoming = new AudioManager ("data:audio/wav;base64, ");
				<!-- let hurdle_meteorSound = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "); -->
				<!-- let hurdle_ballSound = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "); -->
				<!-- let hurdle_rockSound = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "); -->
				<!-- let hurdle_rocketSound = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64,"); -->
				
				let vTouch = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				
				let vLaugh = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				
				let equipGun = new AudioManager ("data:audio/wav;base64, ");
				let hitArray = [];
				
				hitArray.push (
					new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64,"),
					new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "),
					new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "),
					new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "),
					new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, "),
				);
				
				let chaseSound = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let karmaDead = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				
				let hero_pain = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let karma_laugh = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let karma_whisper = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				let hero_karma = new AudioManager ("data:audio/mp3;base64, ");
				
				
				// hurdles -- triggered by the boss
				let hurdleArray = [];
				for (let i = 0; i < MAX_NO_OF_HURDLES; i++) {
					hurdleArray.push (new Hurdles());
				}
				
				let powerup1 = new Powerup ();
				

				<!-- for (let i = 0; i < MAX_NO_OF_HURDLES; i++) { -->
					<!-- hurdleArray[i].setHurdles (); -->
				<!-- } -->
			</script>
			
			<!-- main game loop -->
			<script>
				let quit = true;
				let karma_processing = false;
				let showKarma = false;
				
				
				
				
				<!-- karma.condition = true; -->
				<!-- karma.setHigherBeing (); -->
				function runMainProgram () {
					setInterval (function () {
						
						powerup1.show = true;
						<!-- console.log ("The program is reading here"); -->
					}, 7000);	
					
					
					setTimeout (function (e) {
						showKarma = true;
					}, 10000);
					
					function animate () {
						// clearing the screen
						ctx.clearRect (0, 0, SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT);
						
						// rendering image
						background.render (0, 0, SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT, 0, 0, SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT);
						
						
						
						hero.doingWhat(karma, gun);
						gun.renderGun ();
						gun.renderBullet (hero, karma);
						
						karma.showHigherBeing (hero);
						
						// detecting collision between hero and karma
						if (checkCollision (hero, karma)) {
							// decrease hero's health
							hero.health -= karma.damage;
							
							vTouch.play ();
							
							karma.condition = false;
							karma_processing = false;
							
							karma.setHigherBeing (hurdleArray);
						}
						
						
						if (showKarma) {
						
							if (!karma.condition && !karma_processing) {
								
								karma.setHigherBeingTimeout ();
								
								setTimeout (function () {
								karma.setHigherBeing (hurdleArray);
									karma.condition = true;
									karma_processing = false;
									BULLET_SPEED = MIN_BULLET_SPEED;
									<!-- chaseSound.stop(); -->
								}, karma.Time_Out);
								
								chaseSound.stop();
								BULLET_SPEED = MAX_BULLET_SPEED;
								karma_processing = true;
								<!-- karma.y = 0; -->
							}
						}
						
						// collision detection between hurdles
						for (let j = 0; j < MAX_NO_OF_HURDLES; j++) {					
							hurdleArray[j].checkHurdleCollision (hero);
							
							hurdleArray[j].updateHurdle ();
							
						}
							
							
						// setting timeout for the Powerup
						if (powerup1.show) {
							powerup1.getPowerup();
							powerup1.show = false;
						}
						
						powerup1.renderPowerup (hero);
						
						
						
						hero.charJumping();
						
						if (hero.x  > SCREEN_WIDTH) {
							hero.x = 0;
						}
						if (hero.x + CHARACTER_WIDTH  < 0) {
							hero.x = SCREEN_WIDTH;
						}
						
						if (!quit) {					
							requestAnimationFrame (animate);
						}
					}
					
					
					animate ();
				
				}
			</script>
			
			<!-- taking inputs -->
			<script>
				document.addEventListener ("keydown", function (e) {
					e.preventDefault ();
					
					switch (e.key) {
						case "a":
							if (!gun.reloading) {
							
								hero.action = "run";
								if (!gun.isEquipped) {
									hero.x -= hero.Speed + 3;
								} else {
									hero.x -= hero.Speed;
								}
								hero.direction = "left";
								click.play ();
							}
							break;
						case "d":
							if (!gun.reloading) {
							
								hero.action = "run";
								if (!gun.isEquipped) {
								
									hero.x += hero.Speed + 3;
								} else {
									hero.x += hero.Speed;
								}
								hero.direction = "right";
								click.play();
							}
							break;
						case "w":
							hero.action = "jump_up";
							hero.animeDelay = 0;
							jump.play ();
							
							if (!hero.jumping) {							
								hero.jumping = true;
							}
							<!-- hero.							-->
							break;
						case " ":
							if (!gun.isEquipped) {
								equipGun.play();
							} else {							
								if (!gun.reloading ) {								
									gun.shootBullet ();
								}
							}
							break;
						case "r":
							gun.reloading = true;
							gun.reloadBullet ();
							break;
						case "s":
							console.log ("Go gym do Squats");
							hero.action = "idle";
							break;
							
						case "q":
							if (gun.isEquipped) {
								gun.isEquipped = false;
								gun_unequip.play ();
							} else {
								gun.isEquipped = true;
								gun_equip.play ();
							}
						<!-- default: -->
							<!-- console.log ("Press 'a', 'd', or 'w'"); -->
							<!-- break; -->
					}
					
				})
				
				document.addEventListener ("click", function (evt) {
					evt.preventDefault ();
					
					let mouse_x = evt.clientX;
					let mouse_y = evt.clientY;
					
					if ((mouse_x > hero.x) && (mouse_x < hero.x + CHARACTER_WIDTH) && (mouse_y > hero.y) && (mouse_y < hero.y + CHARACTER_HEIGHT)) {
						// shoot
						if (gun.isEquipped) {
							if (!gun.reloading) {							
								gun.shootBullet ();
							}
						}
					} else if (mouse_x < SCREEN_WIDTH / 2 && mouse_y > SCREEN_HEIGHT / 2) {
					
						if (!gun.reloading) {
						
							hero.action = "run";
							hero.x -= hero.Speed;
							hero.direction = "left";
							click.play ();
						}
					} else if (mouse_x > SCREEN_WIDTH / 2 && mouse_y > SCREEN_HEIGHT / 2) {
						if (!gun.reloading) {
						
							hero.action = "run";
							hero.x += hero.Speed;
							hero.direction = "right";
							click.play ();
						}
					} else if (mouse_y < SCREEN_HEIGHT /2 ) {
						hero.action = "jump_up";
						jump.play ();
						hero.animeDelay = 0;
							
						if (!hero.jumping) {							
							hero.jumping = true;
						}
					}
					
				})
				
			</script>
			<br><br>
			<p style="color: white;">Press 'reload' to play again.</p><br><br>
			<button id="play">PLAY THE GAME</button><br><br>
			<button id="Info">How to Play</button><br><br>
			<button id="show">What the?</button><br><br> <br>
			
			<div id="info_box" style="border: 1px solid grey; color: white;">
			<br>
				Information:<br>
				<ol>
					<li>The game is supposed to only take one input at a time so you may not be able to get 2 key presses. (No jumping with side strafe)</li>
					<li>You can dodge bullets either by jumping or facing the same direction as the bullet. (Bullet grazing left - You face left / You turn your back to bullet)</li>
					<li>You can also shoot bullet with bullet to cancel them out. </li>
					<li>Your bullets will deal damage to yourself. The powerful the bullet the more damage the bullet deals.</li>
					<li>At max, you can have 12 lives and 4 damage per bullet.</li>
					<li>You can apply same principle to the obstacles (as to bullets) to dodge them. </li>
					<li>You cannot shoot down obstacles only dodge them.</li>
					<li>Going from left to right / vice versa will lead to a loop back.</li>
					<li>The being is same as you. It won't take damage when it's back is turned to the bullet.<br>
					(I originally intended it to be opposite but it made the game too difficult. However, you can change the source code as you like.)</li>
					<li></li>
				</ol>
			
				Press 'a' and 'd' to move left and right respectively.<br>
				Press 'w' to jump. <br>
				Press 'Space' to shoot. <br>
				Press 'r' to reload. (You cannot move while reloading ~ 3s). <br>
				Press 'q' to equip/unequip the gun. (You move faster without the gun). <br>
				<br><br><br>
				<h2>For touch Screens</h2>
				Tap 'right' of the screen to move right. <br>
				Tap 'left' of the screen to move left. <br>
				Tap 'up' of the screen to jump. <br>
				Tap 'Character' to shoot. <br>
				Reload is automatic. <br>
				* Cannot switch guns.

			</div>

			<script>
				const info_box = document.getElementById ("info_box");
				const show_box = document.getElementById ("show_box");
				
				
				info_box.style.display = "none";
				show_box.style.display = "none";
				
				<!-- runMainProgram (); -->
				
				// for the buttons
				document.getElementById ("play").addEventListener ("click", function (e) {
					e.preventDefault ();
					
					quit = false;
					runMainProgram ();
				})
				
				document.getElementById ("Info").addEventListener ("click", function (e) {
					<!-- info_box.setAttribute ("display", "block"); -->
					
					if (info_box.style.display == "block") {
					
						info_box.style.display = "none";
					} else {
						info_box.style.display = "block";
					}
				})
				
				document.getElementById ("show").addEventListener ("click", function (e) {
					if (show_box.style.display == "block") {
						show_box.style.display = "none";
					} else {
						show_box.style.display = "block";
					}
				})
			</script>
